        {
          "text": "This cutting drill is a three-count exercise that uses a sottano to link both the mandritto and riverso fendenti, and teaches the close interrelation between the fendente and sottano: you can strike one and instantly return along the same line with the complementary cut without having to step or reorient the body. This allows for very fast, compound attacks."
